data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span` of native-sized integers.** Both `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>` work as expected:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signedSpan   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsignedSpan = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

The test confirmed correct allocation, assignment, and iteration. On this 64-bit system, `nint` is 8 bytes. No `unsafe` context is needed — `stackalloc` into a `Span<T>` is safe in modern C#.
